params.amount: the amount to deposit                 if you want to deposit ETH, send the                 amount + gas fee to use in the cross chain message
params.options: the options to send with the message for defaullt                  we recommend to use 2000 wei as gas fee and send                  200000 gwei for paying the gas (only for LayerZero)
params.solutionId: the solution id to use for sending the message                     1 -- Axelar                     2 -- CCIP                     3 -- Hyperlane                     4 -- LayerZero
params.token: the address of the token to deposit, 0x0 for ETH

params.amountIn: amount of the token to send
params.poolv3: address of the uniswap v3 pool
params.secondsAgo: the seconds ago to use for the calculation
params.tokenIn: address of the token to send

params.priorityFee: the priorityFee to send to the white fisher
params.signature: the signature of the user who wants to send the message                   a signature is contructed with a message like this:                  "addressToReceive,nonce,priorityFee,amount"
params.tokenAddress: address of the token to deposit

params.priorityFee: the priorityFee to send to the white fisher

handle(uint32,bytes32,bytes).details: function to receive the deposit from Hyperlane

lzReceive((uint32,bytes32,uint64),bytes3.details: Entry point for receiving messages or packets from the endpoint.Entry point for receiving msg/packet from the LayerZero endpoint.

params._executor: The address of the executor for the received message.
params._extraData: Additional arbitrary data provided by the corresponding executor.
params._guid: The unique identifier for the received LayerZero message.
params._message: The payload of the received message.
params._origin: The origin information containing the source endpoint and sender address.  - srcEid: The source chain endpoint ID.  - sender: The sender address on the src chain.  - nonce: The nonce of the message.

nextNonce(uint32,bytes32).details: _srcEid The source endpoint ID._sender The sender address.The path nonce starts from 1. If 0 is returned it means that there is NO nonce ordered enforcement.Is required by the off-chain executor to determine the OApp expects msg execution is ordered.This is also enforced by the OApp.By default this is NOT enabled. ie. nextNonce is hardcoded to return 0.

oAppVersion().details: Providing 0 as the default for OAppSender version. Indicates that the OAppSender is not implemented. ie. this is a SEND only OApp.If the OApp uses both OAppSender and OAppReceiver, then this needs to be override returning the correct versions.

returns.receiverVersion: The version of the OAppReceiver.sol contract.
returns.senderVersion: The version of the OAppSender.sol contract.

NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.tokenAddress: the address of the token to see

setDelegate(address).details: Only the owner/admin of the OApp can call this function.Provides the ability for a delegate to set configs, on behalf of the OApp, directly on the Endpoint contract.Defaults to the owner of the OApp.

params._delegate: The address of the delegate to be set.

setPeer(uint32,bytes32).details: Only the owner/admin of the OApp can call this function.Indicates that the peer is trusted to send LayerZero messages to this OApp.Set this to bytes32(0) to remove the peer address.Peer is a bytes32 to accommodate non-evm chains.

params._peer: The address of the peer to be associated with the corresponding endpoint.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Should indicate whether the contract implements IAny2EVMMessageReceiver e.g. return interfaceId == type(IAny2EVMMessageReceiver).interfaceId || interfaceId == type(IERC165).interfaceId This allows CCIP to check if ccipReceive is available before calling it. If this returns false or reverts, only tokens are transferred to the receiver. If this returns true, tokens are transferred and ccipReceive is called atomically. Additionally, if the receiver address does not have code associated with it at the time of execution (EXTCODESIZE returns 0), only tokens will be transferred.

returns._0: true if the interfaceId is supported

params.newOwner: the address of the new owner
